post_text:
The Twin Valley Board of Education made a difficult decision and has approved a change in the last day of school. It has been moved to May 8, 2015. This decision was based on the financial plight of the district. The district has few fiscal reserves to endure the present mid year unplanned financial cuts recently signed into law.

Student athletics/activities will continue past May 8th. The building principals and athletic directors will be communicating with patrons and will use School Messenger frequently to communicate important updates and messages to you. Please watch for more updates pertaining to date changes for activities or events that may be effected.

If you have questions, please plan for your child's building administrator to be the liaison for communication, but know that you can also contact the Superintendent of Schools or a board of education member. Thank you for your support of the Twin Valley School District.

post_text: January is School Board Appreciation Month and I wanted to take a few minutes to say thank you to each of our board members for all of the time that they spend, without getting paid, focused on providing the best possible education for the children of USD #240. Most people in the community do not see how much time these individuals devote to their volunteer job of being a school board member. They spend countless hours each week reading the latest news out of Topeka, studying data reports, evaluating budget documents, and thinking about how to improve our district. If you see one of our school board members out and about in the community, please take a minute to thank them for their service to the students and families within USD #240.

post_text: USD 240 has a position opening for a Food Service Coordinator. The successful candidate should have at least two years management experience (preferably in food service), proficient with computers, excellent communication and people skills, and budget/reporting abilities. This is a 35hr/wk 10 month position that is benefit and KPERS eligible. To apply, fill out classified application at www.usd240.org>district>humanresources and submit cover letter, resume, and references to dbetts@usd240.org. Applications are due by September 5, 2014.

post_text: New for fall 2014! Seventh and eighth grade students at Tescott and Bennington schools will each be issued an iPad for student instruction with parent/guardian consent. The iPads were approved by the board of education as an instructional tool and as a part of the curriculum at the June 2014 board meeting. The purchase of the iPads were a result of a district approved pilot which took place last spring. There will be technology fees associated with the student issued iPads. We are excited about using new digital resources and increasing student personalization and mobile learning. Please call the school or district office if you have questions.

post_text:
The Bennington Junior High competed in the HOA Music Festival on: Tuesday, March 11th at Ell-Saline Middle School.

The 8th grade Choir - received a I - Superior Rating and the 7th/8th grade Band also received a I - Superior Rating.

We also had individual Soloists:

Vocal Soloists -

Alexis Watson - 8th grader - Received a I - Superior Rating
Rhianna Masenthin - 8th grader - Received a II - Excellent Rating

Instrumental Soloists -

Shara Shepard - 8th grader - Received a I - superior rating (Flute)
Katie Dreiling - 8th grader - Received a I - Superior rating (Alto Saxophone)
Micah Dolloff - 8th grader - Received a II - Excellent rating (Snare Drum)

Congratulations to the Instructors:
Mrs. Theresa Cannefax - Vocal Instructor
Mrs. Paula Serrien - Accompanist
Miss Bailey Altman - Instrumental Instructor

Congratulations to All!!!

post_text: Mr. Piepho's and Mr. Trout's 5th grade class has been studying the basic unit of life, cells. The class constructed edible cells using gelatin, marshmallows, grapes and raisins. The class also built a foldable book to organize their notes and looked at cells under a microscope. Mr. Piepho's 6th grade is studying the Physical Sciences. The class just finished an experiment on density where the class brought in various liquids and mixed them together to see what happens. The various groups were surprised at the results. Next, they will learn about physical and chemical changes. Science Rocks!!
